page.title: 02WORCESTERSHIRE ANIMALS
page.content:
Inhabitants of this area are lovers of animals.
There are no less than three kennels: one breeding, boarding and trimming Cocker and King Charles Spaniels; another breeding and boarding the Mittina strain of American Cocker, King Charles and Field Spaniels; and a third keeping Finnish Spitz, a type of small husky of which there are no more than 200 in the United Kingdom.
Also in this area is Arlebroc Aristocats, a boarding cattery - Arlebroc being the Anglo-Saxon name for the area.
